  "management45": "Critical operational constraints are flagged at 3 airports right now. No engine anti-ice operations are currently flagged. Across base airports: 1 critical, 9 high, 11 medium, 18 normal. Key bases needing attention include Katowice Wojciech Korfanty (KTW/EPKT), Gdańsk Lech Wałęsa (GDN/EPGD) and Larnaca (LCA/LCLK); plus 7 other bases. 11 additional base airports are at medium severity and should be monitored closely. At base airports, the dominant pattern is thunderstorm / convective risk, mist and fog / freezing fog  — most notably around David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Tuzla (TZL/LQTZ) and Varna (VAR/LBWN). Network hotspots: Tenerife Sur (TFS/GCTS), Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO). Primary drivers: low cloud base and snow / blowing snow. Expected impact is reduced runway capacity with higher delay and diversion risk, especially where visibility/RVR and cloud base are very low. Since the last update, 12 airports changed status, led by Frankfurt-Hahn (HHN/EDFH), David the Builder Kutaisi (KUT/UGKO), Francisco de Sá Carneiro (OPO/LPPR) and 9 others.",
